Date: Thu, 29 Jan 2026 12:57:29 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 08/22] fix(core): Handle Azure AD roles array format in OIDC
 provisioning

This fix addresses issues with OIDC/SSO role provisioning when using
Azure AD (Microsoft Entra ID) as the identity provider:

1. Instance role provisioning now accepts arrays
   - Azure AD sends all App Roles as an array in the 'roles' claim
   - Filters for 'global:*' roles when given an array
   - Prioritizes roles: owner > admin > member

2. Project role provisioning filters out global roles
   - Skips entries starting with 'global:' to prevent parsing
     'global:admin' as projectId='global', role='admin'
   - Logs debug message explaining global roles are handled separately

Cherry-picked from fix/oidc-azure-ad-provisioning branch (bf960798d0)
